SIMPLE: prohibitionist
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prohibitionist
<hw>Pro`hi*bi"tion*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who favors prohibitory duties on foreign goods
in commerce; a protectionist.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who favors the prohibition of the sale (or of
the sale and manufacture) of alcoholic liquors as beverages.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prohibitive</ent>⟦br⟧
